    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p> <p>Heat a&nbsp;large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the<strong> bacon</strong> and cook for 2 min on each side or until crispy</p> <p>Remove the <strong>bacon</strong> from the pan, roughly chop into small pieces and set aside &ndash; this is your<strong> bacon topping</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p> <p>Peel and chop&nbsp;the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Trim, then dice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p> <p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large pot with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>&nbsp;over a medium heat</p> <p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and cook for 5 min or until softened</p> <p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong>&nbsp;with half the&nbsp;<strong>chopped garlic</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 2 min further</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken&nbsp;stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 700ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.3L]</span>&nbsp;<strong>boiled water</strong></p> <p>Add the <strong>chicken&nbsp;stock</strong>, <strong>cannellini beans</strong> and <strong>kale</strong> to the pan and bring to the boil over a high heat</p> <p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 10 min &ndash; this is your <strong>vegetable &amp; bean soup</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basil leaves</strong>&nbsp;to a <strong>pestle &amp; mortar</strong> with the&nbsp;<strong>remaining&nbsp;garlic</strong>&nbsp;(Don't like raw garlic? Go easy!) and grind to a smooth<strong>&nbsp;paste</strong></p> <p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil </strong>and give it a good mix up</p> <p>Tip: if you don't have a pestle &amp; mortar, chop the basil leaves very finely and mix with olive oil</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Grate the <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p> <p>Add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> to the<strong>&nbsp;basil paste </strong>and give everything a good mix up<strong>&nbsp;</strong>&ndash;&nbsp;this is your <strong>pistou</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>ciabatta roll</strong><strong>s&nbsp;</strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 5 min or until warmed through</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/courgette-bean-and-bacon-soup-with-ciabatta/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>vegetable &amp; bean soup</strong> with a spoonful of the <strong>pistou</strong>, topped with the<strong> crispy bacon</strong> and the <strong>ciabatta rolls</strong>&nbsp;on the side</p> <p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
